dct_title_s: Braunswyck et Meydburg cum terris adjacentibus; sculpersunt E. S. Hamersveldt et S. Rogeri.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Illustrations around the title cartouche depict a woman holding wheat and fruit and a cherub pouring wine into a glass held by a man. From "Atlantis maioris appendix", Johannes Janssonius, 1630. 1 map; 37 x 47 cm.
dct_rights_sm: This map is in the public domain.
